IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: CHILDCARE RESOURCES' MISSION IS TO MAKE QUALITY CARE AND EDUCATION OF CHILDREN HAPPEN BY PROVIDING INFORMATION, EDUCATION AND ASSISTANCE TO FAMILIES, PROVIDERS OF CHILD CARE AND THE COMMUNITY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: CHILDCARE RESOURCES' MISSION IS TO MAKE QUALITY CARE AND EDUCATION OF CHILDREN HAPPEN BY PROVIDING INFORMATION, EDUCATION AND ASSISTANCE TO FAMILIES, PROVIDERS OF CHILD CARE AND THE COMMUNITY.
IRS990.Desc: TRAINING AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE - TRAINING SESSIONS, COURSES AND CONFERENCES ARE OFFERED FOR PROVIDERS TO ASSIST THEM IN MEETING THE NEEDS OF CHILDREN IN THEIR CARE. TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IS AVAILABLE TO CURRENT AND POTENTIAL PROVIDERS LOOKING TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF CARE BEING PROVIDED, OPEN A NEW CHILD CARE PROGRAM OR SEEK CDA OR NATIONAL ACCREDITATION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: SUPPLEMENTAL CHILD CARE PROGRAM - PROVIDES TUTITION ASSISTANCE TO WORKING FAMILIES WHO ARE OVER INCOME TO RECEIVE STATE SUBSIDIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: INFANT TODDLER PROGRAM - OFFERS ASSISTANCE TO CHILD CARE CENTERS THAT WANT TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF CARE IN THEIR INFANT AND TODDLER CLASSROOMS.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: RISE - OFFERS ASSITANCE TO CHILD CARE PROGRAMS INTERESTED IN WORKING TOWARDS NATIONAL ACCREDIDATION STANDARDS AND IMPROVING QUALITY OF EARLY CARE THEY OFFER AT THEIR CHILD CARE CENTER. EARLY LEARNING RESOURCE VAN/CENTER - OFFERS AN ARRAY OF RESOURCES AND SERVICES FOR EARLY CARE EDUCATORS.RESOURCE AND REFERRAL - PROVIDES INFORMATION AND MATERIALS TO ASSIST PARENTS/FAMILIES IN PARENTING THEIR CHILDREN. RESOURCES OFFER CHILD DEVELOPMENT INFORMATION, INCLUDING AGE-APPROPRIATE EXPECTATIONS, ACTIVITIES AND POSITIVE PARENTING PRACTICES, AMONG OTHER TOPICS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018, THE AGENCY HAD NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT QUALIFY FOR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE AGENCY FILES ANNUAL FORM 990 WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AND ITS TAX RETURN FOR THE YEAR ENDED 2015 AND SUBSEQUENT YEARS REMAIN SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY HAS MEMBERS OF ITS BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS OF THE AGENCY'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE ELECTED BY THE OTHER MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A MEETING WAS HELD WITH THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, AND THE ACCOUNTANT WHO PROVIDED A COPY OF THE 990 TAX RETURN TO THE AGENCY. THE 990 WAS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BEFORE IT WAS FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY HAS EACH OFFICER SIGN A DISCLOSURE STATEMENT REGARDING CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. THE DISCLOSURES ARE REVIEWED FOR ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND ANY CONFLICTS NOTED ARE ADDRESSED BY THE AGENCY'S BYLAWS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE INDEPENDENT BOARD OF DIRECTORS SETS AND REVIEWS THE SALARY FOR THE AGENCY'S OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND 990 AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST BY AN INDIVIDUAL OR CORPORATION.
THERE WAS NOT ANY CHANGES MADE TO THE AUDIT OVERSIGHT PROCESS IN THE CURRENT YEAR.
